# Abdi Adama School IMS Project Plan

This document is the working master plan for building the Abdi Adama School Integrated Management System.

The current requirements are broad and some parts are still under construction, so this plan is designed to be flexible. It separates the project into phases, defines the architecture, and shows the order we should build things in so we can move fast without creating a messy system.

## 1. Project Goal

Build a modern web-based School Integrated Management System that manages school operations in one place.

The system should support:

- Student records and admissions
- Class, subject, timetable, and exam management
- Attendance tracking for students and staff
- Parent and student portals
- Messaging and notifications
- HR and payroll
- Fees, accounting, and reporting
- Inventory, assets, and transport
- RBAC security and backups
- Future-ready LMS and AI modules

The first version should be practical, stable, and easy to expand later.

## 2. Product Strategy

### 2.1 Build in Layers

We should not try to finish everything at once. The best approach is:

1. Core platform first
2. Academic operations next
3. Communication and finance next
4. Operations and reporting next
5. Advanced modules after the foundation is stable

### 2.2 Prioritize Real Usage

The system should focus on what the school will use daily:

- Admissions
- Student profiles
- Class assignment
- Timetables
- Attendance
- Exams and report cards
- Parent communication
- Fees and financial visibility

### 2.3 Keep the Architecture Modular

Every major feature should live in its own domain so the app stays maintainable.

Recommended domains:

- Auth and access control
- Student information
- Academic structure
- Attendance
- Exams and grading
- LMS
- Communication
- HR
- Finance
- Inventory and assets
- Transport
- Reporting and analytics
- System settings

