## 4. Technical Direction

### 4.1 Recommended Stack

For a fast web-first build, use:

- Frontend: Next.js
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- UI system: shadcn/ui or equivalent component library
- Database: PostgreSQL
- ORM: Prisma or Drizzle
- Authentication: Auth.js or Supabase Auth
- Hosting: Vercel for app, managed PostgreSQL provider for database
- File storage: Supabase Storage or S3-compatible storage
- Validation: Zod
- Forms: React Hook Form

### 4.2 Why This Stack

- One codebase is faster to ship
- Strong TypeScript support reduces bugs
- Next.js is good for dashboards and forms
- PostgreSQL fits structured school data very well
- The system can grow into a larger platform later

### 4.3 Architecture Style

Use a modular monolith first.

This means:

- One app
- One database
- Clear module boundaries
- Shared auth and design system
- Internal APIs or server actions for business logic

This is simpler than splitting into microservices too early.

