## 12. Development Standards

### Code Organization

- Group code by domain
- Keep shared utilities small and focused
- Separate data access from UI where practical
- Use reusable form and table components

### Quality Standards

- Type safety everywhere possible
- Validation on both client and server
- No business logic hidden in the UI only
- No direct database access from random components
- Every sensitive action must be authorized

### Version Control

- Use clear feature branches
- Commit in small logical units
- Protect the main branch later

